body:
I'm encountering an error when attempting to use skopeo to download a Bicep image from my Azure Container Registry (ACR). Here's the command and the resulting error message:

```shell
skopeo copy docker://my_azure_acr_.azurecr.io/microsoft.managedidentity/userassignedidentities:2.0.854 docker-archive:mycontainer.tar
Getting image source signatures
Copying blob 87307ff27cb6 done
FATA[0000] creating an updated image manifest: unsupported image-specific operation on artifact with type "application/vnd.ms.bicep.module.config.v1+json" 
```

Sample bicep module manifest:

```json
{
  "schemaVersion": 2,
  "mediaType": "application/vnd.oci.image.manifest.v1+json",
  "artifactType": "application/vnd.ms.bicep.module.artifact",
  "config": {
    "mediaType": "application/vnd.ms.bicep.module.config.v1+json",
    "digest": "sha256:44136fa355b3678a1146ad16f7e8649e94fb4fc21fe77e8310c060f61caaff8a",
    "size": 2,
    "annotations": {}
  },
  "layers": [
    {
      "mediaType": "application/vnd.ms.bicep.module.layer.v1+json",
      "digest": "sha256:87307ff27cb6e37656c8561038dcdef7da85fc9681fb915e207b2a8208e85ca3",
      "size": 1722,
      "annotations": {
        "org.opencontainers.image.title": "Compiled ARM template"
      }
    }
  ],
  "annotations": {
    "org.opencontainers.image.created": "2024-03-19T09:36:33.9692853Z"
  }
}
```


Environment:
Skopeo version: 
```shell
skopeo --version
skopeo version 1.13.3
```
